<TITLE> CAO to open flood-tracking cell </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 28 (bdnews24.com) -- A monitoring cell to be established at the Chief Adviser's Office will keep track of the overall flood situation in the country, a spokesman said Saturday. Following a decision at a meeting at the CAO Saturday, deputy commissioners were directed to send information on river waters and floods quickly to the monitoring cell. "The food and disaster management ministry and the army have two separate cells to monitor the flood situation. Apart from this, a new cell will be opened at the office of the Chief Adviser," the chief adviser's press secretary Syed Fahim Munaim told bdnews24.com by telephone. "The cell will keep the chief adviser informed about the flood situation round the clock." Sources in the Chief Adviser's Office said the meeting had discussed the river situation throughout the country. The chief adviser was apprised of the preparations to face the situation. He was told that relief was adequate and could be distributed quickly if necessary. Food and disaster management adviser Tapan Chowdhury and local government adviser Anwarul Iqbal were present at the meeting. bdnews24.c
